{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/12956", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/12956/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/12956/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/12956/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/12956", "id": 372739769, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MjI0ODQ0NzE3", "number": 12956, "title": "Fix \"CUDA Tensor __rsub__ breaks when device is not 0\"", "user": {"login": "yf225", "id": 4063635, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQwNjM2MzU=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/4063635?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225", "html_url": "https://github.com/yf225", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/yf225/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2018-10-22T23:23:19Z", "updated_at": "2018-11-23T15:53:27Z", "closed_at": "2018-10-30T23:30:45Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "pull_request": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/pulls/12956", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/12956", "diff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/12956.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/12956.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>Currently, <code>a = 1 - torch.tensor([1]).to('cuda:1')</code> puts <code>a</code> in <code>cuda:1</code> but reports <code>a.device</code> as <code>cuda:0</code> which is incorrect, and it causes illegal memory access error when trying to access <code>a</code>'s memory (e.g. when printing). This PR fixes the error.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #10850.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"353803422\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/10850\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/10850/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/10850\">#10850</a>.</p>", "body_text": "Currently, a = 1 - torch.tensor([1]).to('cuda:1') puts a in cuda:1 but reports a.device as cuda:0 which is incorrect, and it causes illegal memory access error when trying to access a's memory (e.g. when printing). This PR fixes the error.\nFixes #10850.", "body": "Currently, `a = 1 - torch.tensor([1]).to('cuda:1')` puts `a` in `cuda:1` but reports `a.device` as `cuda:0` which is incorrect, and it causes illegal memory access error when trying to access `a`'s memory (e.g. when printing). This PR fixes the error.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/10850.\r\n"}